Best Books of 2020-2022

Greg Jackson

December 2022

These are my favourite books that I’ve read over the past 3 years, since I started keeping a record of what I’ve been reading. I’ve gone for some separation of categories to make it easier to peruse.

Special Categories

These authors are separated from the other lists because their work is so consistently good (to my taste), that they would otherwise dominate my lists.

Richard Wagamese

  • Keeper’n Me - Fiction
  • Ragged Company - Fiction
  • Indian Horse - Fiction
  • Medicine Walk - Fiction
  • Starlight - Fiction
  • A Perfect Likeness - Fiction
  • One Native Life - Non-Fiction
  • One Story, One Song - Non-Fiction
  • Embers - Non-Fiction
  • What Comes From Spirit - Non-Fiction

Becky Chambers

  • The Long Way to a Small Angry Planet - Wayfarers #1
  • A Closed and Common Orbit - Wayfarers #2
  • Record of a Spaceborn Few - Wayfarers #3
  • The Galaxy, and the Ground Within - Wayfarers #4
  • To Be Taught, If Fortunate
  • A Psalm for the Wild Built - Monk and Robot #1
  • A Prayer for the Crown Shy - Monk and Robot #2

Fredrik Backman

  • A Man Called Ove
  • My Grandmother Sends Her Regards and Apologizes
  • Britt-Marie Was Here
  • Anxious People
  • Beartown - Beartown #1
  • Us Against You - Beartown #2
  • The Winners - Beartown #3
